**Raw results IPv4 routing test cases**

- **[Top] Network Topologies:** TG-DUT1-TG 3-node circular topology  with single links between nodes.

- **[Enc] Packet Encapsulations:** Eth-IPv4 for L3 IPv4 routing.

- **[Cfg] DUT configuration:** DUT1 run the DPDK l3fwd application  DUT1 tested with Intel-XXV710.

- **[Ver] TG vefication:** In MaxReceivedRate tests TG sends traffic at  line rate and reports total received packets over trial period.  Test packets are generated by TG on  links to DUTs. TG traffic profile contains two L3 flow-groups  (flow-group per direction, 253 flows per flow-group) with all packets  containing Ethernet header, IPv4 header with IP protocol=61 and static  payload. MAC addresses are matching MAC addresses of the TG node  interfaces.
